import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.hist(data['US_Gross'], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='US Gross')
    ax.hist(data['Worldwide_Gross'], bins=20, alpha=0.5, label='Worldwide Gross')
    ax.axvline(data['US_Gross'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='US Gross Mean')
    ax.axvline(data['Worldwide_Gross'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Worldwide Gross Mean')
    ax.set_xlabel('Gross Earnings')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?')
    ax.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Running_Time_min'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Running_Time_min'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Running_Time_min'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Running_Time_min'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (min)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre']]
    data = data.groupby(['MPAA_Rating', 'Major_Genre']).size().reset_index(name='count')
    data = data.pivot(index='MPAA_Rating', columns='Major_Genre', values='count')
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.set_xlabel('MPAA Rating')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating and Major_Genre?')
    ax.legend(title='Major_Genre', bbox_to_anchor=(1.0, 1.0))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
